Automation

   Automation build.
     * [https://ant.apache.org/]Apache Ant - Automation build tool,
       similar to make, written in Java.
     * [http://maven.apache.org/]Apache Maven - Build automation tool
       mainly for Java.
     * [http://www.bazel.io/]Bazel - Google's build system.
     * [http://www.gnu.org/software/make/]GNU Make - The most popular
       automation build tool for many purposes.
     * [http://gradle.org/]Gradle - Another build automation system.
     * [https://github.com/ruby/rake]Rake - Build automation tool similar
       to Make, written in and extensible in Ruby.

Backups

   Backup software.
     * [http://www.amanda.org/]Amanda - Client-server model backup tool.
     * [http://www.bareos.org/en/]Bareos - A fork of Bacula backup tool.
     * [http://backuppc.sourceforge.net/]BackupPC - BackupPC is a
       high-performance system for backing up to disk.
     * [https://labs.riseup.net/code/projects/backupninja]Backupninja -
       Lightweight, extensible meta-backup system.
     * [http://www.pgbarman.org/]Barman - Backup and Recovery Manager for
       disaster recovery of PostgreSQL servers.
     * [https://github.com/borgbackup/borg]BorgBackup - A fork of
       [https://attic-backup.org/]Attic deduplicating backup program
       written in Python.
     * [http://burp.grke.org/]Burp - Network backup and restore program.
     * [http://duplicity.nongnu.org/]Duplicity - Encrypted
       bandwidth-efficient backup using the rsync algorithm.
     * [https://github.com/elkarbackup/elkarbackup]Elkarbackup - Backup
       solution based on RSnapshot with a simple web interface
     * [https://github.com/axkibe/lsyncd]Lsyncd - File Monitor which
       spawns a process to synchronize the changes (rsync by default).
     * [https://rclone.org/]rclone - a command line program to sync files
       and directories to and from several cloud storage
       systems/providers.
     * [http://www.nongnu.org/rdiff-backup/]Rdiff-backup - An easy A
       remote incremental backup of all your files.
     * [http://rsnapshot.org/]Rsnapshot - Filesystem Snapshotting Utility.
     * [https://github.com/starkandwayne/shield]Shield - A pluggable
       architecture for backup and restore of database systems.
     * [http://www.snebu.com/]Snebu - Snapshot backup with global
       multi-client deduplication and transparent compression.
     * [http://www.urbackup.org/]UrBackup - Another client-server backup
       system.
     * [https://github.com/dojo4/drebs]DREBS - AWS EBS backup script that
       supports strategies.
     * [http://zbackup.org/]ZBackup - A versatile deduplicating backup
       tool.

Build and software organization tools

   Build and software organization tools.
     * [https://easybuild.readthedocs.org/en/latest/]EasyBuild - EasyBuild
       builds software and modulefiles for High Performance Computing
       (HPC) systems in an efficient way.
     * [https://www.tacc.utexas.edu/research-development/tacc-projects/lmo
       d]environment-modules Lmod - Lmod is a Lua based module system that
       easily handles the MODULEPATH Hierarchical problem.
     * [http://hpcbios.readthedocs.org/en/latest/]HPCBIOS - HPCBIOS is an
       effort to setup a common, well-documented and reproducible,
       environment spanning across multiple HPC systems & sites, inclusive
       of documentation.

ChatOps

   Conversation-driven development and management. See
   [https://www.reddit.com/r/chatops]https://www.reddit.com/r/chatops for
   more information.
     * [https://github.com/CloudBotIRC/CloudBot]CloudBot - The simple,
       fast, expandable Python IRC bot.
     * [http://www.eggheads.org/]Eggdrop - the world's most popular IRC
       bot, designed for flexibility and ease of use, and is freely
       distributable under the GNU GPL.
     * [http://errbot.io/]Err - a plugin based chatbot designed to be
       easily deployable, extensible and maintainable.
     * [https://hubot.github.com/]Hubot - A customizable, life
       embetterment robot.
     * [https://github.com/djosephsen/lazlo]Lazlo - A chatops automation
       framework in Go.
     * [https://www.lita.io/]Lita - A robot companion for your company's
       chat room.
     * [https://github.com/itsabot/abot]Abot - A digital assistant
       framework in Go.

Client management

   Managing software on desktop computers.
     * [https://chocolatey.org/]Chocolatey - Windows CLI package manager
       written in .NET/PS, based on [https://www.nuget.org/]NuGet.
     * [http://just-install.it/]just-install - Python script for
       downloading and silently installing MSI files.
     * [http://www.ocsinventory-ng.org/en/]OCS Inventory NG - Inventory,
       deployment and network scan.
     * [http://www.opsi.org/]Opsi (open PC server integration) - Client
       Management for Windows based on Debian.
     * [https://dev.tranquil.it/wiki/WAPT_-_apt-get_pour_Windows/en]WAPT -
       Network-wide (un)installation, configuration and upgrades of
       Windows based software.
     * [http://wpkg.org/]WPKG - Software deployment, upgrade and removal
       program for Windows.

Cloning

   Cloning software.
     * [http://clonezilla.org/]Clonezilla - Partition and disk
       imaging/cloning program.
     * [https://www.fogproject.org/]Fog - Another computer cloning
       solution.

Cloud Computing

     * [https://github.com/AppScale/appscale]AppScale - Cloud software
       with Google App Engine compatibility.
     * [http://archipelproject.org/]Archipel - Manage and supervise
       virtual machines using Libvirt.
     * [http://cloudstack.apache.org/]CloudStack - Cloud computing
       software for creating, managing, and deploying infrastructure cloud
       services.
     * [http://cobbler.github.io/]Cobbler - Cobbler is a Linux
       installation server that allows for rapid setup of network
       installation environments.
     * [http://cc1.ifj.edu.pl/]Cracow Cloud One - Polish Private Cloud -
       The CC1 system provides a complete solution for Private Cloud
       Computing.
     * [http://www8.hp.com/us/en/cloud/helion-eucalyptus-overview.html]HPE
       Helion Eucalyptus - Private cloud software with AWS compatibility.
     * [https://flynn.io/]Flynn - PaaS
     * [http://mesos.apache.org/]Mesos - Develop and run
       resource-efficient distributed systems.
     * [http://opennebula.org/]OpenNebula - User-driven cloud management
       platform for sysadmins and devops.
     * [http://www.openshift.org/]Openshift - PaaS product from Red Hat.
     * [https://www.openstack.org/]OpenStack - Build private and public
       clouds.
     * [http://theforeman.org/]The Foreman - Complete lifecycle management
       tool for physical and virtual servers. FOSS.
     * [https://tsuru.io/]Tsuru - Tsuru is an extensible Platform as a
       Service software.

Cloud Orchestration

     * [http://bosh.io/docs/]BOSH - IaaS orchestration platform originally
       written for deploying and managing Cloud Foundry PaaS, but also
       useful for general purpose distributed systems.
     * [https://www.cloudfoundry.org/]Cloud Foundry - A
       Platform-as-a-Service suite to provide the orchestration services
       that make distributed apps a powerhouse of awesomeness.
     * [http://getcloudify.org/]Cloudify - TOSCA-based cloud orchestration
       software platform written in Python and YAML.
     * [http://www.cloudslang.io/]CloudSlang - Flow-based orchestration
       tool for managing deployed applications, with Docker capabilities.
     * [https://github.com/starkandwayne/genesis]Genesis - A template
       framework for multi-environment BOSH deployments.
     * [https://jujucharms.com/]Juju - Cloud orchestration tool which
       manages services as charms, YAML configuration and deployment
       script bundles.
     * [http://kubernetes.io/]Kubernetes - Orchestration system for Docker
       containers - ([https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes]Source
       Code, [http://kubernetes.io/docs/]Documentation) Apache Go
     * [https://puppet.com/mcollective]MCollective - Ruby framework to
       manage server orchestration, developed by Puppet labs.
     * [http://andrewchilds.github.io/overcast/]Overcast - Deploy VMs
       across different cloud providers, and run commands and scripts
       across any or all of them in parallel via SSH.
     * [http://rundeck.org/]Rundeck - Simple orchestration tool.
     * [http://saltstack.com/]Salt - Fast, scalable and flexible systems
       management software written in Python/ZeroMQ.
     * [https://github.com/geofffranks/spruce]Spruce - A tool that merges
       separate YAML files into one. Works well with
       [https://github.com/starkandwayne/genesis]Genesis.
     * [https://stackstorm.com/]StackStorm - Event Driven Operations and
       ChatOps platform for infrastructure management. Written in Python.
     * [https://www.terraform.io/]Terraform - Terraform works with many
       cloud providers and creates infrastructure from code.

Code Review

   Web Based collaborative code review system.
     * [https://www.gerritcodereview.com/]Gerrit - Based on the Git
       version control, it facilitates software developers to review
       modifications to the source code and approve or reject those
       changes.
     * [http://phabricator.org/]Phabricator - Code review tool build by
       facebook and used by WikiMedia, FB, dropbox etc. Comes with an
       integrated wiki, bug tracker, VC integration and a CLI tool called
       arcanist.
     * [https://www.reviewboard.org/]Review Board - Available as free
       software under the MIT License.

Collaborative Software

   Collaborative software or groupware suites.
     * [http://www.citadel.org/]Citadel/UX - Collaboration suite
       (messaging and groupware) that is descended from the Citadel family
       of programs.
     * [http://www.egroupware.org/start.html]EGroupware - Groupware
       software written in PHP.
     * [http://www.horde.org/apps/groupware]Horde Groupware - PHP based
       collaborative software suite that includes email, calendars, wikis,
       time tracking and file management.
     * [https://kolab.org/]Kolab - Another groupware suite.
     * [http://www.sogo.nu/]SOGo - Collaborative software server with a
       focus on simplicity and scalability.
     * [https://www.zimbra.com/open-source-email-overview/]Zimbra -
       Collaborative software suite, that includes an email server and web
       client.

Configuration Management Database

   Configuration management database (CMDB) software.
     * [http://www.i-doit.org/]i-doit - IT Documentation and CMDB.
     * [http://www.combodo.com/itop-193]iTop - Complete ITIL web based
       service management tool.
     * [https://github.com/allegro/ralph]Ralph - Asset management, DCIM
       and CMDB system for large Data Centers as well as smaller LAN
       networks.
     * [https://github.com/clusto/clusto]Clusto - Helps you keep track of
       your inventory, where it is, how it's connected, and provides an
       abstracted interface for interacting with the elements of the
       infrastructure.
     * [http://tumblr.github.io/collins/]Collins - At Tumblr, it's the
       infrastructure source of truth and knowledge.
     * [https://github.com/digitalocean/netbox]netbox - IP address
       management (IPAM) and data center infrastructure management (DCIM)
       tool

Configuration Management

   Configuration management tools.
     * [http://www.ansible.com/]Ansible - It's written in Python and
       manages the nodes over SSH.
     * [https://cfengine.com/]CFEngine - Lightweight agent system.
       Configuration state is specified via a declarative language.
     * [https://www.chef.io/chef/]Chef - It's written in Ruby and Erlang
       and uses a pure-Ruby DSL.
     * [http://palletops.com/]Pallet - Infrastructure definition,
       configuration and management via a Clojure DSL.
     * [https://puppet.com/]Puppet - It's written in Ruby and uses
       Puppet's declarative language or a Ruby DSL.
     * [http://saltstack.com/]Salt - It's written in Python.
     * [http://www.steve.org.uk/Software/slaughter/]Slaughter - It's
       written in Perl.

Continuous Integration & Continuous Deployment

   Continuous integration/deployment software.
     * [http://buildbot.net/]Buildbot - Python-based toolkit for
       continuous integration.
     * [https://github.com/AnalogJ/capsulecd]CapsuleCD - CD script for
       automating package/library releases (npm, cookbooks, gems, pip,
       jars, etc).
     * [http://concourse.ci/]concourse - A modern tool to gain visibility
       on the CI/CD pipeline. The flexible, declarative DSL is easy to
       learn and powerful to use.
     * [https://github.com/drone/drone]Drone - Continuous integration
       server built on Docker and configured using YAML files.
     * [https://about.gitlab.com/gitlab-ci/]GitLab CI - Based off of ruby.
       They also provide GitLab, which manages git repositories.
     * [http://www.go.cd/]Go - Continuous delivery server.
     * [http://jenkins-ci.org/]Jenkins - An extendable continuous
       integration server.

Control Panels

   Web hosting and server or service control panels.
     * Web hosting
          + [https://froxlor.org/]Froxlor - Easy to use panel for Linux
            with Nginx and PHP-FPM support.
          + [http://www.ispconfig.org/]ISPConfig - Hosting control panel
            for Linux.
          + [http://sentora.org/]Sentora - Control panel for Linux, BSD,
            and Windows based on ZPanel.
          + [http://vestacp.com/]VestaCP - Hosting panel for Linux but
            with Nginx.
          + [http://www.virtualmin.com/]Virtualmin - Hosting panel for
            Linux based on webmin.
     * DNS
          + [http://atomiadns.com/]Atomia DNS - DNS management system.
          + [https://github.com/tuxis-ie/nsedit]nsedit - nsedit is a DNS
            editor for PowerDNS, working with PowerDNS's new API.
          + [https://github.com/odoucet/pdns-gui]PDNS Gui - WebGUI which
            aids in administering domains and records for PowerDNS with
            MySQL.
          + [http://www.poweradmin.org/]Poweradmin - Friendly web-based
            DNS administration tool for PowerDNS server.
     * Revision Control
          + [http://svnadmin.insanefactory.com/]iF.SVNAdmin - WebGUI to
            manage Subversion repositories and User/Group permissions.
          + [https://www.scm-manager.org/]SCM-Manager - The easiest way to
            share and manage your Git, Mercurial and Subversion
            repositories.
          + [http://www.websvn.info/]WebSVN - Opensource web subversion
            repository browser.
     * Virtualization
          + [http://feathur.com/]Feathur - VPS Provisioning and Management
            Software.
          + [http://panamax.io/]Panamax - Project that makes deploying
            complex containerized apps as easy as Drag-and-Drop.
          + [https://github.com/sibprogrammer/owp]OpenVZ Web Panel - Web
            panel to control OpenVZ virtual machines.
          + [https://retspen.github.io/]WebVirtMgr - libvirt-based Web
            interface for managing virtual machines.
     * Server
          + [http://ajenti.org/]Ajenti - Control panel for Linux and BSD.
          + [http://cockpit-project.org/]Cockpit - New multi-server web
            interface for Linux servers written in C.
          + [http://www.webmin.com/]Webmin - Linux server control panel.

Deployment Automation

   Tools and scripts to support deployments to your servers.
     * [http://capistranorb.com/]Capistrano - Deploy your application to
       any number of machines simultaneously, in sequence or as a rolling
       set via SSH (rake based).
     * [http://www.fabfile.org/]Fabric - Python library and cli tool for
       streamlining the use of SSH for application deployment or systems
       administration tasks.
     * [http://nadarei.co/mina/]Mina - Really fast deployer and server
       automation tool (rake based).
     * [https://www.munki.org/munki/]munki - Webserver-based repository of
       packages and package metadata, that allows macOS administrators to
       manage software installs.
     * [http://rocketeer.autopergamene.eu/]Rocketeer - PHP task runner and
       deployment tool.
     * [https://github.com/pressly/sup/]sup - Super simple deployment tool
       - just Unix - think of it like 'make' for a network of servers.
     * [https://github.com/seattlerb/vlad]Vlad the Deployer - Deployment
       automation (rake based).

Distributed Filesystems

   Network distributed filesystems.
     * [https://camlistore.org/]Camlistore - A set of open source formats,
       protocols, and software for modeling, storing, searching, sharing
       and synchronizing data.
     * [http://ceph.com/]Ceph - Distributed object store and file system.
     * [http://drbd.linbit.com/]DRBD - Distributed Replicated Block
       Device.
     * [http://leo-project.net/]LeoFS - Unstructured object/data storage
       and a highly available, distributed, eventually consistent storage
       system.
     * [http://www.gluster.org/]GlusterFS - Scale-out network-attached
       storage file system.
     * [https://github.com/ipfs/go-ipfs]Go IPFS - Implementation of
       [http://ipfs.io/]IPFS, a global, versioned, peer-to-peer filesystem
       that seeks to connect all computing devices with the same system of
       files.
     * [http://hadoop.apache.org/]HDFS - Distributed, scalable, and
       portable file-system written in Java for the Hadoop framework.
     * [http://lustre.org/]Lustre - Parallel distributed file system,
       generally used for large-scale cluster computing.
     * [http://www.moosefs.org/]MooseFS - Fault tolerant, network
       distributed file system.
     * [http://mogilefs.org/]MogileFS - Application level, network
       distributed file system.
     * [http://www.openafs.org/]OpenAFS - Distributed network file system
       with read-only replicas and multi-OS support.
     * [http://ori.scs.stanford.edu/]Ori Filesystem - A Secure Distributed
       File System built for offline operation.
     * [http://docs.openstack.org/developer/swift/]Swift - A highly
       available, distributed, eventually consistent object/blob store.
     * [https://sheepdog.github.io/sheepdog/]SheepDog - A distributed
       Blockdevice, Rest, QEMU and distributed Filesystem storage.
     * [https://tahoe-lafs.org/trac/tahoe-lafs]TahoeLAFS - secure,
       decentralized, fault-tolerant, peer-to-peer distributed data store
       and distributed file system.
     * [http://www.xtreemfs.org/]XtreemFS - XtreemFS is a fault-tolerant
       distributed file system for all storage needs.

DNS

   DNS servers.
     * [https://www.isc.org/downloads/bind/]Bind - The most widely used
       name server software.
     * [http://cr.yp.to/djbdns.html]djbdns - A collection of DNS
       applications, including tinydns.
     * [https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Designate]Designate - DNS REST API
       that support several DNS servers as its backend.
     * [http://www.thekelleys.org.uk/dnsmasq/doc.html]dnsmasq - A
       lightweight service providing DNS, DHCP and TFTP services to
       small-scale networks.
     * [https://www.knot-dns.cz/]Knot - High performance
       authoritative-only DNS server.
     * [http://www.nlnetlabs.nl/projects/nsd/]NSD - Authoritative only,
       high performance, simple name server.
     * [https://www.powerdns.com/]PowerDNS - DNS server with a variety of
       data storage back-ends and load balancing features.
     * [http://unbound.net/]Unbound - Validating, recursive, and caching
       DNS resolver.
     * [http://www.yadifa.eu/]Yadifa - Lightweight authoritative Name
       Server with DNSSEC capabilities powering the .eu top-level domain.

Domains

   Domain management.
     * [https://domainmod.org/]DomainMOD - Manage your domains and other
       internet assets in a central location.

Editors

   Open source code editors.
     * [https://atom.io/]Atom - A hackable text editor from Github.
     * [http://brackets.io/]Brackets - Code editor for web designers and
       front-end developers.
     * [http://www.eclipse.org/]Eclipse - IDE written in Java with an
       extensible plug-in system.
     * [http://www.geany.org/]Geany - GTK2 text editor.
     * [http://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/]GNU Emacs - An extensible,
       customizable text editor-and more.
     * [http://pad.haroopress.com/]Haroopad - Markdown editor with live
       preview.
     * [https://icecoder.net/]ICEcoder - Code editor awesomeness, built
       with common web languages.
     * [https://github.com/jdleesmiller/jotgit]jotgit - Git-backed
       real-time collaborative code editing.
     * [https://www.kdevelop.org/]KDevelop - IDE by the people behind KDE.
     * [http://lighttable.com/]Light Table - The next generation code
       editor.
     * [http://limetext.org/]Lime - Aims to provide an open source
       solution to Sublime Text
     * [https://notepad-plus-plus.org/]Notepad++ - GPLv2 multi-language
       editor with syntax highlighting for Windows.
     * [https://github.com/textmate/textmate/]TextMate - A graphical text
       editor for OS X.
     * [http://www.vim.org/]Vim - A highly configurable text editor built
       to enable efficient editing.
     * [https://code.visualstudio.com/]Visual Studio Code - An open source
       cross-platform extensible code editor from Microsoft
     * [http://nano-editor.org/]Nano - Easy to use, customizable text
       editor.

Identity Management

   LDAP servers and other tools to manage accounts and identities.

LDAP

     * [http://www.port389.org/]389 Directory Server - Developed by Red
       Hat.
     * [http://directory.apache.org/]Apache Directory Server - Apache
       Software Foundation project written in Java.
     * [http://freeradius.org/]FreeRADIUS - High performance and highly
       configurable multi-protocol policy/authentication server,
       supporting RADIUS, DHCPv4 and VMPS.
     * [http://opendj.forgerock.org/]OpenDJ - Fork of OpenDS.
     * [https://opends.java.net/]OpenDS - Another directory server written
       in Java.
     * [http://www.OpenLDAP.org/]OpenLDAP - Developed by the OpenLDAP
       Project.
     * [http://www.freeipa.org/]FreeIPA - Based on 389-DS. Includes
       Kerberos, DNS, as well as host based access control.

Tools and web interfaces

     * [https://www.fusiondirectory.org/]Fusion Directory - Improve the
       Management of the services and the company directory based on
       OpenLDAP.
     * [https://indieauth.com/]Indieauth - Sign in with your domain name
       (using the rel-me-auth protocol).
     * [https://www.libravatar.org/]Libravatar - Libravatar is a service
       which delivers your avatar (profile picture) to other websites.
     * [https://www.ldap-account-manager.org/lamcms/]LDAP Account Manager
       (LAM) - Web frontend for managing entries (e.g. users, groups, DHCP
       settings) stored in an LDAP directory.
     * [http://openid.net/developers/libraries/]OpenID - A Simple Identity
       layer on top of OAuth 2.0.
     * [http://osiam.github.io/]OSIAM - Secure identity management
       solution providing REST based services for authentication and
       authorization.
     * [https://www.samba.org/]Samba - Active Directory and CIFS protocol
       implementation.
     * [https://bounca.org/]BounCA - A personal SSL Key / Certificate
       Authority web-based tool for creating self-signed certificates.

IT Asset Management

   IT Assets Management software.
     * [http://www.glpi-project.org/spip.php?lang=en]GLPI - Information
       Resource-Manager with an additional Administration Interface.
     * [http://www.ocsinventory-ng.org/en/]OCS Inventory NG - Enables
       users to inventory their IT assets.
     * [http://www.opsi.org/]OPSI - Hardware and software inventory,
       deployment, and patching for Linux and Windows.
     * [http://racktables.org/]RackTables - Datacenter and server room
       asset management like document hardware assets, network addresses,
       space in racks, networks configuration.
     * [https://github.com/allegro/ralph]Ralph - Asset management, DCIM
       and CMDB system for large Data Centers as well as smaller LAN
       networks.
     * [https://snipeitapp.com/]Snipe IT - Asset & license management
       software.

Log Management

   Log management tools: collect, parse, visualize ...
     * [https://www.elastic.co/]Elasticsearch - A Lucene Based Document
       store mainly used for log indexing, storage and analysis.
     * [http://www.fluentd.org/]Fluentd - Log Collector and Shipper.
     * [https://flume.apache.org/]Flume - Distributed log collection and
       aggregation system.
     * [http://goaccess.io/]GoAccess - Real-time web log analyzer and
       interactive viewer that runs in a terminal or through the browser.
       ([https://github.com/allinurl/goaccess]Source Code) MIT C
     * [https://www.graylog.org/]Graylog - Pluggable Log and Event
       Analysis Server with Alerting options.
     * [http://mozilla-services.github.io/hindsight/]Hindsight - Stream
       processing system which may be used for log aggregation (Replaces
       Heka).
     * [https://www.elastic.co/products/kibana]Kibana - Visualize logs and
       time-stamped data.
     * [https://www.elastic.co/products/logstash]Logstash - Tool for
       managing events and logs.
     * [http://www.octopussy.pm/]Octopussy - Log Management Solution
       (Visualize / Alert / Report).

Mail Clients

     * [http://www.claws-mail.org/]Claws Mail - Old school email client
