     * [https://www.mozilla.org/de/thunderbird/]Thunderbird - Free email
       application that's easy to set up and customize.

Monitoring

   Monitoring software.
     * [http://adagios.org/]Adagios - Web based Nagios interface for
       configuration and monitoring (replacement to the standard
       interface), and a REST interface,
       [https://github.com/opinkerfi/adagios]SourceCode,
       [https://github.com/opinkerfi/adagios/wiki]Documentation)
     * [https://github.com/guardian/alerta]Alerta - Distributed, scaleable
       and flexible monitoring system.
     * [https://bloonix.org/]Bloonix - Bloonix is a monitoring solution
       that helps businesses to ensure high availability and performance.
       GPLv3 Perl
     * [http://bolo.niftylogic.com/]bolo - A Do-it-Yourself monitoring
       framework built to gather metrics, mine data and report on the
       systems in your network.
     * [http://bosun.org/]Bosun - Monitoring and alerting system by Stack
       Exchange ([https://github.com/bosun-monitor/bosun]Source Code,
       [http://bosun.org/quickstart.html]Documentation) MIT Go
     * [http://www.cacti.net/]Cacti - Web-based network monitoring and
       graphing tool.
     * [http://cabotapp.com/]Cabot - Monitoring and alerts, similar to
       PagerDuty.
     * [https://github.com/google/cadvisor]cadvisor - Analyzes resource
       usage and performance characteristics of running containers
       ([https://github.com/google/cadvisor]Source Code) Apache Go
     * [http://mathias-kettner.com/check_mk.html]check_mk - Collection of
       extensions for Nagios.
     * [https://github.com/afaqurk/linux-dash]Dash - A low-overhead
       monitoring web dashboard for a GNU/Linux machine.
     * [http://www.ezservermonitor.com/]eZ Server Monitor - A lightweight
       and simple dashboard monitor for Linux, available in Web and Bash
       application.
     * [http://flapjack.io/]Flapjack - Monitoring notification routing &
       event processing system.
     * [https://healthchecks.io/]Healthchecks - Monitoring for cron jobs,
       background services and scheduled tasks.
     * [https://www.icinga.org/]Icinga - Nagios fork that has since lapped
       nagios several times. Comes with the possibility of clustered
       monitoring - ([https://github.com/Icinga]Source Code) - GPLv2
     * [http://www.librenms.org/]LibreNMS - Fully featured network
       monitoring system that provides a wealth of features and device
       support.
     * [http://mmonit.com/monit/#home]Monit - Small utility for managing
       and monitoring Unix systems.
     * [http://munin-monitoring.org/]Munin - Networked resource monitoring
       tool.
     * [http://www.naemon.org/]Naemon - Network monitoring tool based on
       the Nagios 4 core with performance enhancements and new features.
     * [https://www.nagios.org/]Nagios - Computer system, network and
       infrastructure monitoring software application.
     * [https://github.com/eleme/bell.js]Node-Bell - Real-time anomalies
       detection for periodic time series, metrics monitor.
     * [http://www.observium.org/]Observium - SNMP monitoring for servers
       and networking devices. Runs on linux.
     * [http://omdistro.org/]OMD - The Open Monitoring Distribution.
     * [http://pcp.io/]Performance Co-Pilot - Lightweight, distributed
       system performance and analysis framework.
     * [https://phpsysinfo.github.io/phpsysinfo/]PhpSysInfo - A
       customizable PHP script that displays information about your system
       nicely.
     * [https://www.phpservermonitor.org/]PHP Server Monitor - Open source
       tool to monitor your servers and websites
     * [https://github.com/Jahaja/psdash]psdash - A linux system
       information web dashboard using psut ils and flask.
     * [https://k3oni.github.io/pydash/]pyDash - Small web-based
       monitoring dashboard for linux.
     * [http://riemann.io/]Riemann - Flexible and fast events processor
       allowing complex events/metrics analysis.
     * [https://github.com/rapidloop/rtop]rtop - an interactive, remote
       system monitoring tool based on SSH.
     * [https://sensuapp.org/]Sensu - Monitoring framework.
     * [https://github.com/BotoX/ServerStatus]ServerStatus BotoX - Display
       and monitor your servers statistics in a beatiful way.
     * [https://github.com/mojeda/ServerStatus]ServerStatus moejda -
       Server Status website script, displays uptime (days), free RAM,
